org.jlinalg.rationalFunction

Class RationalFunctionFactory<BASE extends IRingElement<BASE>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlinalg.RingElementFactory<RationalFunction<BASE>>
      • org.jlinalg.rationalFunction.RationalFunctionFactory<BASE>
  • Type Parameters:
    BASE -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, IRingElementFactory<RationalFunction<BASE>>

    public class RationalFunctionFactory<BASE extends IRingElement<BASE>>
extends RingElementFactory<RationalFunction<BASE>>
    The factory for rational functions. The factory has to be created for a particular sub-type of IRingElement, that is the constructors of single elements have to be provided with a factory of this type.

    Note: if the factory of the base type is not a singelton factory, it must implement java.lang.Object.equal(Object o) such that if the base type are considered equal, the factories are equal.

    Author:
    Andreas Keilhauer

    Serialized Form
